            <div type="a">
                <column>1</column>
                <head>Products of the North and South</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt>So long as the South has such champions in the North we need not despair of
                    the Union.</excerpt>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Review of an address given by Spencer Banks before New York Merchants
                    exchange. Banks argues that the slaveholding states produce more "material
                    wealth" than the nonslaveholding stattes, and should be entitles to difrect the
                    government. SS says his figures are absurd. Praises Ruggles for challenging
                    Banks and defending the South.</summary>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>2</column>
                <head>Narrow Escape</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Crawford</ln>
                        <pf>Magnus W.</pf>
                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>Central RR cars narrowly avoided hitting a boulder that had fallen on the
                    tracks.</summary>
            </div>
            <div type="l">
                <column>4</column>
                <head>For the Spectator; Adventures in the Snow (concluded)</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Gooch</ln>
                        <fn>Stapleton</fn>
                        <pf>Capt.</pf>
                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>Continuation of Gooch's story from 2/4/57; escape from the train stuck in
                    the January snow.</summary>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>3</column>
                <head>A Country Darkey's First Visit to a Lawyers Office</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Lawyers in town tease a free black from Barterbrook; arrest him for public
                    whistling while Court was in session. They demanded a fine from him; and he ran
                    home in fear.</summary>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>3</column>
                <head>The Thaw</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Cold snap finally breaks on 2/5/57, but the suddenness of the thaw led to
                    flooding and the destruction of bridges across Middle River.</summary>
            </div>
            <pageNote>Report on PA senatorial race; From Europe in col. 3.; Bottom of page is very
                dark, blurry; Congressional report in col. 7.</pageNote>
        </page>
